default across departments, focusing on the central oversight of Defra and the Cabinet Office, and in June 2013 we made another commitment to extend that scrutiny to look at sustainability in individual departments. With significant audit and briefing support from the NAO, we have examined the position in BIS [and will soon be examining the Home Office.] The BIS audit prompted that department to fill a vacant ‘sustainability champion’ post and we understand from the NAO and Defra that other departments, faced with NAO/EAC audits, are refining their sustainable development structures and processes. 
