defaultOur most recent visit in December 2012 allowed us to discuss evolving discussions in the European Commission on possible action on a particular type of agricultural pesticide, as part of our inquiry on 
defaultPollinators and Pesticides
default. This opened the way for us to travel to Brussels in April 2013 to discuss the proposed Commission ban on those ‘neonicitinoids’ with the Health &amp; Consumer Affairs Commissioner, who was able to take on board the findings of inquiry before that ban was finally approved. 
